RACE.FOOTNOTES: FRANK THE MAYOR broke alertly to be taken in hand and reserved off a contested pace, rallied four wide through the turn to take command at the top of the lane and draw clear late. LAB RAT dueled on the lead from the rail through the turn and weakened late. DAAHERS BULLY stalked early, dueled on the lead through the turn and faded down the lane. CAYMANS COBRA chased the leaders for a half mile and came up empty to be no factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 6 7 1/2F Turf CR: 98. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 34500. (PLUS UP TO $6,900 Open ATB) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $30,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 l bs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 15, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 15, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000 (Maiden Or Claiming Races Not Considered In Allowances). (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the tur f course, it will be run onthe main track at One Mile. If the race is for two year olds, it will be run at Seven Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROBO set the pace from the inside into the first turn, was in a long drive, cleared the the second turn then drew clear in the stretch and held on well till the end. PARROT HEAD raced in the middle of the field down the backstretch while two wide, then bid from the four path on the far turn into the early stretch, rallied mid way down the lane to close willingly for the place prize. OPTIMAL TRIP was in a long drive to track the place from the inside down the backstretch and into the far turn, then closed belatedly in the stretch just missing second place in the end. BUBBA BLING settled in the two path down the early backstretch, then was bumped by an outer rival, steadied, was bumped again by an inner rival heading into the second turn, then rallied from the four path into the turn to closed strong in the end. FRED'STWIRLINCANDY chased the pace from the inside, was in a hard drive throughout the far turn to rally in the stretch and closed well in the end. WHISKEY NOT WINE settled along the inside down the backstretch, then was bumped by an outer rival, kicked up heels, regained stride, was in a steady drive throughout the far turn. CLIFF DIVER stalked the pace while two wide down the backstretch, then settled back, bid from the two path on the far turn into the stretch then gave way in the end. MALIBU S S settled in the three path down the early backstretch, then steadied off the heels of rival, was taken up and lost momentum throughout the remainder of the course and was no rally. HOOVES YOUR DADDY trailed behind the field throughout the course and was no factor. KISS ME D ORO chased the pace from the three path down the early backstretch, then was pulled up causing contention amongst other rivals, eased and did not finish the race and was vanned off. There was a STEWARD'S INQUIRY in regards to interference on the backstretch. After review, there was no change made to the order of finish.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG WAVE JAMES pressed the pace from the onset, moved two wide to take command in the far turn and drew away when prompted. WHITEROSE JEWEL reserved in mid-pack off the pace early, commenced a rally into the far turn, checked along the rail lacking room, split horses when clear down the lane and finished full of run. RAIL TOWN set the pace away from the gate, led for a half mile and tired turning for home. UPTOWN BIGBADJON raced at the rear of the field and was no factor.
